  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: v1.10.25\r\nOS & Version: OSX (probably will reproduce on all)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nWhen fetching info for a block with `client.BlockByNumber` fails on some L2 chains with:\r\n`transaction type not supported` as the lib fails to parse the transaction types which are not 0, 1 or 2. For example this block on Optimism Goerli testnet:\r\nhttps://goerli-optimism.etherscan.io/txs?block=4567220\r\nI've tested this on Optimism and Arbitrum testnets and they both fail for the same reason.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nFetch the block correctly without failing.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nA minimal example:\r\n```go\r\nfunc main() {\r\n\trpc := \"https://goerli.optimism.io\"\r\n\tclient, err := ethclient.Dial(rpc)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tlog.Fatal(err.Error())\r\n\t}\r\n\tlog.Printf(\"Connected with chain at %s\\n\", rpc)\r\n\tblock, err := client.BlockByNumber(context.Background(), big.NewInt(4061225))\r\n\ttx, _ := client.TransactionReceipt(context.Background(), common.HexToHash(\"0x05165a474a7a6386be0232fce515c793875e91e958133f673588db509dc5ece8\"))\r\n\tlog.Println(tx.Type)\r\n\tif err != nil {\r\n\t\tlog.Println(err)\r\n\t\treturn\r\n\t}\r\n\r\n\tlog.Println(block.Time())\r\n\treturn\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
